## Licensing

### Source Code

All analysis scripts and software components contained in this repository are released under the MIT License.

### Research Materials and Documentation

The following materials are made available under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0), unless otherwise stated:

* S1: Arabic Questionnaire
* S2: Response Bias Assessment
* S3: Psychometric Assessment
* S4: Qualitative Thematic Analysis
* S5: Medicinal Plant Safety Database
* S6: STROBE Checklist
* S7: Statistical Analysis Plan (SAP)
* S8: Data Dictionary & Codebook
* S9: Reproducibility Guide
* S10: Ethics Approval Documentation
* S11: Anonymized Dataset

Users are free to copy, distribute, adapt, and reuse these materials provided appropriate attribution is given to the original authors.

### Data Availability

The anonymized dataset (S11) contains no personally identifiable information and is provided to facilitate transparency, reproducibility, secondary analyses, and educational use.

### Ethical Considerations

Data sharing is consistent with the informed consent obtained from participants and the ethical approval granted by the Biomedical Ethics Committee of the Syrian Herbs & Alternative Medicine Association (SHAMNA), Syria.

**Approval Number:** SHAMNA-26-04
**Approval Date:** 10 April 2026

All participant information was anonymized prior to public release. No attempt should be made to identify individual participants.

### Citation Requirement

Users of the dataset, questionnaire, codebook, supplementary materials, or analysis workflow are requested to cite the associated manuscript and Zenodo archive:

Khatib C, Abo Kaf T, Masri THF, Mathbout N, Zayat Y. *Exploratory Survey of Herbal Medicine Use and Safety Awareness among Digitally Connected Syrian Adults: Implications for Arabic Digital Health Resources.* Submitted to PLOS ONE (2026).

Zenodo Repository DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20777941
